<head><link href="~/css/EnrollmentLandingPage.css" rel="stylesheet" /></head>
<body>
    <!-- Hero Banner with Background Image -->
    <section class="hero-banner">
        <!-- Back Button -->
        <a href="@Url.Action("DashboardPage","Landing")" class="btn back-button" ><img src="~/images/arrow-left.svg" alt="Alternate Text" width="25"/></a>

        <!-- University Header Inside Hero -->
        <div class="university-header">
            <img src="~/images/logo.svg" alt="University Logo" class="university-logo">
            <div class="university-info">
                <h2 class="university-name">State University</h2>
                <p class="university-subtitle">State University</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Hero Content -->
        <div class="hero-content">
            <div class="hero-left">
                <h1 class="system-title">ONLINE<br>ENROLLMENT<br>SYSTEM</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-right">
                <p class="hero-tagline">Future starts here.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Background Image -->
        <img src="~/images/hero-image.svg" alt="Library background" class="hero-background">
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content Container -->
    <div class="content-wrapper">
        
        <!-- Enroll Now Section -->
        <section class="enroll-section">
            <div class="enroll-content">
                <h2 class="enroll-title">ENROLL NOW!</h2>
                <p class="enroll-subtitle">Freshmen & Late Officially Open for  University of Academic Year 2025-2026</p>
                <a href="@Url.Action("EnrollmentDashboard", "Landing")" class="btn-enroll text-decoration-none">Enroll Now</a>
            </div>
            <div class="enroll-image">
                <img src="~/images/background-img1.svg" alt="Happy students" class="students-image">
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Process of Enrollment -->
        <section class="process-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">Process of Enrollment</h2>
            
            <p class="process-intro">
                Each student classification is provided with a dedicated enrollment form to ensure that specific requirements, 
                status conditions, and Subject procedures are accurately addressed. Enrollment includes:
            </p>

            <div class="student-types">
                <p><strong>Regular Students</strong> – students whose course loads (SPH) from the required curriculum sequence 
                has fit simple academic standing or subject availability.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Irregulars</strong> – students whose course loads do not necessarily attended subjects according 
                to the sequence of the trimester or are currently attending in the university the first time.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Returnees</strong> – students who are currently enrolled in the university.</p>
                
                <p><strong>Freshmen</strong> – First-time enrollees who are newly admitted to the university.</p>
            </div>

            <p class="process-note">
                Although the enrollment know are designed to address the fundamental of classification of students follow 
                a standardized sequence of steps. This process may vary slightly depending on the nature of specific academic 
                footwork. the simplicity of all enrollment will remain consistent throughout all courses and programs.
            </p>

            <p class="enrollment-steps-note">All required Enrollment Steps Varies Including the following</p>

            <!-- Three Steps -->
            <div class="steps-grid">
                <div class="step-box">
                    <div class="step-header">
                        <span class="step-num">1</span>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="step-title">Submission and<br>Evaluation</h3>
                    <ul class="step-list">
                        <li>Submission of enrollment form and academic requirements</li>
                        <li>Verification of student documents and academic history clearance</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="step-box">
                    <div class="step-header">
                        <span class="step-num">2</span>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="step-title">Subject and Schedule<br>Assignment</h3>
                    <ul class="step-list">
                        <li>Assigning pre-subjects for evaluation</li>
                        <li>Course information objects from subject worksheets, Subject Load Forms</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="step-box">
                    <div class="step-header">
                        <span class="step-num">3</span>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="step-title">Confirmation and<br>Release</h3>
                    <ul class="step-list">
                        <li>Registration/slot approval if assessment</li>
                        <li>Release of official registration form Certificate of Enrollment</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Other Services -->
        <section class="services-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">Other Services</h2>
            <p class="services-intro">
                Access additional more designed to support your academic journey. From managing your records and monitoring 
                grades to keeping your personal information up to date, these services ensure centralized and reliable way 
                to stay informed and organized throughout your studies.
            </p>

            <!-- Academic Records -->
            <div class="service-box">
                <h3 class="service-title">ACADEMIC RECORDS</h3>
                <p class="service-description">
                    Easily access and review your academic history. Simply centralize tuition, digital grades, and 
                    data dashboard and any administrative requirements of new institution here.
                </p>
                <button class="btn-service" onclick="goToAcademicRecords()">Go to Previous Subjects</button>
                <div class="service-image-container">
                    <img src="~/images/background-img2.svg" alt="Academic Records" class="service-bg-image">
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Student Info -->
            <div class="service-box">
                <h3 class="service-title">STUDENT INFO</h3>
                <p class="service-description">
                    View and manage your personal student details in one place. 
                    From your ID and contact information to your academic status, your profile is always organized and up to date.
                </p>
                <button class="btn-service" onclick="goToStudentInfo()">Go to Student Information</button>
                <div class="service-image-container">
                    <img src="~/images/background-img3.svg" alt="Academic Records" class="service-bg-image">
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>